Text: Thanks for sharing! I'm curious, though: Is this a transcode or the real thing? What's the quality like?
Well everything is a transcode of the lossless CD, but at 320kbs its pretty high quality. Now it won't sound as good as say, lossless or vinyl, but it will be pretty good.
Thanks for the info. I'll definitely check this out; their last record was pretty good..
If you ever get a chance to, see them live.. They sound better than the CD, which is something that is very rare these days.
I swear most artists sound better in real life...
And I agree with the uploader- sounding better live is becoming rare, with all of the overproduced/underskilled music coming out these days.
